.TH "sta32x_hw_params" 9 "sta32x_hw_params" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sta32x_hw_params \- program the STA32X with the given hardware parameters.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sta32x_hw_params
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ","
.BI "struct snd_pcm_hw_params *params "  ","
.BI "struct snd_soc_dai *dai "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
the audio stream
.IP "params" 12
the hardware parameters to set
.IP "dai" 12
the SOC DAI (ignored)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function programs the hardware with the values provided.
Specifically, the sample rate and the data format.
